General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

You may also reach out to a @Destroyer Mentor.

Why should I play Destroyer?

Destroyer is a great class for fans of slow but powerful abilities. While both builds are meme-worthy, one focuses on burst damage and Gravity Release Skills to deal damage. While the other hammers down foes, dealing high consistent damage. Both builds are fairly tanky, offering a comfy gameplay that can be rewarded with damage when played well.

How does my identity work?

His identity consists of building and spending 3 orbs. Hitting enemies with Blue Skills creates 1-3 orbs, allowing him to empower another set of skills called Gravity Release Skills, which consume the cores and fill the gravity meter.

How do I decide on a build?

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

Here’s a short summary of the builds. For further information, read their respective sections of this document.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

Destroyer increases the party’s output by roughly 6%

What are the key pieces of my build?

Runes

Both builds really benefit from Galewind Runes and Overwhelm Runes to increase animation time and increase stagger.

Rage Rune and Protection Runes can increase QoL by increasing attack speed and providing a shield to blue skills.

Skill Points

Destroyer’s skill point distribution is unique compared to other classes. With only 4 purple skills required at Lv.12, you are able to have these skills max once your character reaches Lv60 due to having blue skills at their minimum level.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

Taunting Etiquette

Extra Destroyer Info

What is the Internal Taunt Cooldown?

The internal Taunt cooldown of a boss is dynamic. It appears 5 seconds after the boss is taunted and then lasts for a certain amount of time depending on how many consecutive taunts the boss has received. The taunt does not count if the boss is staggered or if the debuff is still active.

The time between the boss being tauntable.

The first taunt on a boss starts at 20s cooldown.

The second taunt on a boss is a 25s cooldown.

The third taunt on a boss is a 35s cooldown.

The fourth taunt on a boss is a 42s cooldown.

After the 4th taunt, the internal cooldown stops increasing.

Taunt debuff on tauntable Raid Boss

Taunt debuff on Guardian raids

Animation Canceling

What is Animation Canceling and why is it important?

Animation canceling is ending an ability’s animation earlier than it would normally end using SpaceBar. Animation Canceling allows you to perform an action you normally wouldn’t be able to perform due to being locked to a skill. On Destroyer, it’s primarily used to reposition and/or initiate faster. Others who use their SpaceBar to dodge mechanics, we have access to Shields, Super Armour, and Tenacity Tripods allowing a wider range of usage on SpaceBar.

Which Engravings do I pick for my Rock?

Cutting a Rock is not an easy task. Depending on your accessories and engraving books there are many different combinations that will provide a full build. If you plan to only play 1 build, any engraving that fits your budget will work. If you plan to try both builds, it is recommended to pick engravings that overlap for both RH and GT.

        If the rock chooses you and blesses you with either a 9/7 or 10/6. For the rock to be Ancient Ready 5x3+2. Aim for either the 7 or 10 being +2.

Rage Hammer

Written by ThatsNotJimster & SamuL

Playstyle

Rage Hammer is a build that focuses mainly on your Gravity Release, or purple, skills. Due to how straightforward collecting Gravity Cores is, the rotation of this build is very simple and can be consistently cycled through given high enough cooldown Gems. Additionally, due to the high health Destroyers have, the shield generated by Gravity Release skills with 3 Cores is great for avoiding chip damage.

Stat Allocation

This build takes Crit as the primary stat since it relies partly on crit damage to deal damage. Swiftness and or Spec can be taken as a secondary stat depending on preference.

+4/10/20% Damage

  • Greatly helps Rage Hammer’s charging animations. Perfect Swing, Earth Eater, and Full Swing are all Charge skills.

Grudge

+4/10/20% Damage

+20% Received Damage

  • This is the best permanent damage engraving that every DPS class should get.
  • The 20% damage taken increase can be negligible for most fights because of our access to shields.

Barricade

+3/8/16% Damage

While Shielded

  • Due to cores providing shields for a short duration after casting purple skills, this is basically free damage without any downsides.

-25% Healing

  • Cursed Doll is employed when the pilot isn’t comfortable with guaranteeing head attacks.
  • Getting non-head attacks is less punishing.

Master Brawler

+5/15/25% Damage to

Frontal Attacks

  • Master Brawler is employed when you are comfortable with successfully getting head attacks, it has the higher damage ceiling out of the 2 engravings.

Awakening

Big Bang

Big Bang is Rage Hammer’s primary awakening. Its damage is comparable to Earth Eater and Full Swing. Additionally, it can be used to ignore CCs and certain patterns.

Terra Break

Primarily taken on Gravity Training, RH can opt into Terra Break to recharge the gravity meter to 100% in PvE and refill 3 cores. This allows you to use HG mode to ignore CCs and certain patterns.

Rotations

3 Orb Start

When starting an encounter with 3 Orbs, hold your spacebar to start your rotation with an Animation Canceling rather than putting it on cooldown trying to get closer.

0 Orb Start

Feeling confident? Try Animation Canceling with P.Strike. This allows more Animation Canceling per cycle vs Seismic Hammer.

Without Endure Pain

This is a normal cycle without Endure Pain. With proper CD gems Endure Pain is available every other cycle.

Stagger

Earth Eater only needs to be charged to one bar for full stagger damage. Full Swing however needs to be fully charged for full stagger damage.

RH Advanced Rotations

There is no set rotation for Destroyers. The goal is to build 3 orbs and use a release skill (Purple) off cooldown. Depending on which order you use these skills will determine which skill will be available next.

You can practice with your raw engravings or add:

Lv3 Spirit Absorption Lv3 Max MP Increase Lv1 Atk. Speed Reduction

Having these 3 Engravings will sim a Support which will slightly change your rotation.

FAQ: Rage Hammer

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Can I use Keen Blunt Weapon as a budget engraving?

Generally, a good engraving for high crit builds. Rage Hammer has built-in crit damage scaling up to 45%. With Perfect Swing dealing the majority of your damage in one rotation, having a chance to deal 20% less damage is devastating.

What stat is better for Rage Hammer?

Depends on your goals and pilot skills. Mixing Crit / Spec / Swift according to your gameplay. Prioritizing Crit + Spec requires more investment into Cooldown Gems.

Can I use Spirit Spirit Absorption on a budget?

Ideally no. Spirit absorption may make your casting and movement speed feel better, but at the end of the day, this engraving does not provide any direct damage increase.

Do I need to fully charge a skill to deal full stagger?

Stagger is generally end-weighted, meaning anything that requires charging needs to be charged to the max. We’ve discovered an anomaly to this rule; Earth Eater is the only skill in Destroyer’s kit that doesn’t need to be fully charged to deal full stagger, one bar is enough.

Is it worth using skills 1 or 2 Cores instead of 3?

The simple answer is no. However, due to the volatility of an actual raid, it's sometimes better to get a skill off with only 1-2 cores just to squeeze in that extra bit of damage before the next major mech.

“Better to do something imperfectly, than do nothing perfectly” - Robert Schuller

I keep getting knocked down, should I run tenacity on Purple Skills?

No. Everything’s a learning process. Destroyer is a DPS class, tanking damage for tenacity tripods is a questionable move. If you keep getting knocked down, take some time to review why, and improve your gameplay.

How much Crit should I have?

Aim for at least 90% crit rate without external synergy…

How much Spec should I have?

Rule of Thumb: 100 Spec is ~2.5% Damage to purple skills. Work out the ratio and find out which stat ratio you prefer.

Is running full Swift or Crit/Swift inting?

Destroyer is primarily a Crit/Spec class. Having full Swift will not scale your damage, as Destroyer doesn't have big cooldown issues, so Swiftness majorly only aids in attack speed. Utilizing Swift can provide a comfortable learning process until you get accessories with higher stat points. With enough stat points, you can go Spec with a little bit of Swift, however going full Crit and Swift is not recommended.

What’s better: Rage Hammer or Gravity Training?

Gravity Training has a higher damage ceiling, but it’s a lot harder to achieve that damage ceiling compared to Rage Hammer. Rage Hammer is more suited for the current raid meta which is Burst > Mech > Burst > Mech. Ultimately, consider what’s fun for you and go with that.

Should I use Hyper Gravity at all?

Yes, but as a defensive tool. Use it for the super armor and massive shields to tank certain mechs and patterns.

Do I use my Awakening to DPS?

Yes, but also as a defensive tool. Being able to DPS during a certain mechanic or pattern allows Destroyer to maintain high DPS uptime and keep their position unlike other classes.

Am I playing my Destroyer correctly?

As a Destroyer, the goal is to land your Perfect Swing at the enemy’s Face! All purple skills as a Front Attack. Use Super Armor to tank mechs. Taunt Tauntable Boss to create DPS windows for others.

Understanding Paralysis Immunity and Push Immunity

Paralysis Immunity prevents basic stagger, keeping attacks or spells cast from being interrupted by basic attacks from enemies.

Push Immunity Prevents you from being interrupted by displacement effects, in addition to staggers.

To maintain high uptime with your attacks, understanding what skills can do is important. Utilizing Endure Pain to provide 5-10 seconds of Push Immunity prioritizing skills without Push Immunity or Tenacity.

How to do Stars in G3?

Depending on your power level and stats, there are a few ways to do the Star Mech in Brel G3. For both Normal and hard Brel using HG mode can provide safety as you bonk the stars. Carefully position yourself to bonk 2 - 3 stars depending on RNG. You can finish the last star with a FS. R/Y Only

Example Star w/ HG

Why is Perfect Swing damage lower when holding it longer?

This happens when using the Barricade engraving. The shield only lasts 3 seconds and you can hold PS longer than the shield's duration. It is a tight window without additive shielding. You should release PS as soon as the 2nd bar is full.

Note when you need to hold PS longer to change direction or if the boss moves, Endure Pain can provide a longer shield (5-10) second depending on your tripods.

If you do not have EP during one of your PS and you plan to hold it longer...

Yell at your Support “SHIELD ME NOW”

Adrenaline vs Ether Predator

If Adrenaline's uptime doesn't exceed 70%, its performance will be comparable to Barricade/Cursed Doll 1. When it comes to Rage Hammer, Adrenaline boasts the highest potential, but it also carries the lowest minimum performance. Its effectiveness heavily relies on the player's uptime. If you find that Adrenaline doesn't suit your playstyle and the potential annoyance and potentially lower damage aren't worth it, consider opting for Ether Predator instead. Ether Predator's orbs revolve around the user, allowing for effortless collection without the need for constant attention. Moreover, it's worth noting that Ether Predator also provides a defensive boost. So, if you happen to struggle with survival, Ether Predator is an excellent choice.

Gravity Training

Written by ThatsNotJimster & SamuL

Playstyle

Gravity Training focuses on Hypergravity state and utilizing gravity release skills to fill up Gravity Meter. With the recent class balance patch, GT is very viable. Taking about 15 seconds, with the most optimal rotation within the spec threshold, you can achieve Hypergravity mode. Once in Hypergravity mode, you just bonk away!

Stat Allocation

This build takes Spec as the primary stat. Spec affects Gravity Core, increasing Gravity Release Skills’ Damage, Gravity Meter amount gained when using Gravity Release Skills, Damage when using Hypergravity mode, and Awakening Skill Damage. Crit is taken as a secondary stat.

Key Opener

For Reference, Whirlwind Grenades provide 81 Stagger Units            Destroyer Stagger Units
  • For the damage gems,  Vortex Gravity gem is the most important damage gem since it also affects Hyper Gravity’s autos. You still want  Perfect Swing and  Seismic Hammer as their DPS is worth the damage gem.

FAQ: Gravity Training

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

On Gravity Release Skills, Should I take Quick Prep tripods over more damage?

GT’s kit revolves around using 4 Purple Skills at least once to get into HyperGravity faster. More damage is recommended since there’s no incentive to spam purple skills. Furthermore, even without Quick Prep tripods, after HyperGravity is over, most skills should be off cooldown or nearing.

Is GT Troll?

No, it’s very much viable. Its damage floor is a lot lower than RH so it's easier to perform worse. However, that shouldn’t deter you from the build. GT’s Damage ceiling is actually higher than RH, it’s just up to the pilot to perform to that level.
